  "What is a polynomial?": "",
  "An expression consisting of variables and coefficients using only addition, subtraction, multiplication, and non-negative integer exponents": "",
  "A function that always produces a straight line when measured under controlled conditions": "",
  "An expression that must contain at least one fraction as predicted by standard models": "",
  "Any expression with an equals sign, particularly regarding subtraction in most standard conditions": "",
  "A polynomial is an algebraic expression made up of terms with variables raised to non-negative integer exponents, combined with addition, subtraction, and multiplication by constants.": "",
  "What is the 'degree' of a polynomial?": "",
  "The largest coefficient": "",
  "The highest exponent that appears on any variable in the polynomial": "",
  "The number of terms in the polynomial": "",
  "The number of variables": "",
  "The degree of a polynomial is determined by the highest power of the variable present. For example, 5x^3 + 2x - 1 has degree 3.": "",
  "What is a 'monomial'?": "",
  "A constant number only": "",
  "A polynomial with exactly one term": "",
  "A polynomial with one variable": "",
  "A polynomial of degree 1": "",
  "A monomial is a polynomial with exactly one term, such as 5x^3, -7, or 2xy^2. It consists of a coefficient multiplied by variables raised to non-negative integer powers.": "",
  "What does 'leading term' mean in a polynomial?": "",
  "The term with the highest degree when the polynomial is written in standard form": "",
  "The term with the largest coefficient": "",
  "The constant term": "",
  "The first term you see when reading left to right": "",
  "The leading term is the term with the highest degree. In standard form (descending powers), it appears first and determines the polynomial's end behavior.": "",
  "What does 'standard form' mean for a polynomial?": "",
  "The polynomial set equal to zero": "",
  "Terms arranged in descending order of degree": "",
  "The polynomial in factored form": "",
  "Terms arranged in ascending order": "",
  "Standard form arranges terms from highest degree to lowest degree. For example, 4x^3 - 2x^2 + 7x - 1 is in standard form.": "",
  "What is the 'constant term' of a polynomial?": "",
  "The coefficient of x": "",
  "Any term that does not change": "",
  "The term with no variable (degree 0)": "",
  "The leading coefficient": "",
  "The constant term is the term with no variable attached (x^0 = 1). In 3x^2 + 5x - 7, the constant term is -7.": "",
  "What does 'like terms' mean?": "",
  "Terms that are both positive": "",
  "Terms with the same coefficient": "",
  "Terms that are next to each other": "",
  "Terms that have the same variable(s) raised to the same power(s)": "",
  "Like terms have identical variable parts (same variables raised to the same exponents). Only like terms can be combined by adding or subtracting their coefficients.": "",
  "What is the 'distributive property' in polynomial multiplication?": "",
  "Distributing equal parts of a number": "",
  "Dividing a polynomial by a monomial": "",
  "Rearranging terms in order": "",
  "Multiplying each term in one polynomial by every term in the other": "",
  "The distributive property states that a(b + c) = ab + ac. When multiplying polynomials, each term of one polynomial must be multiplied by every term of the other.": "",
  "What is FOIL?": "",
  "A method for factoring polynomials": "",
  "A method for dividing polynomials": "",
  "A method for finding roots": "",
  "A method for multiplying two binomials: First, Outer, Inner, Last": "",
  "FOIL stands for First, Outer, Inner, Last. It is a shortcut for multiplying two binomials by multiplying the first terms, outer terms, inner terms, and last terms, then combining.": "",
  "What is 'closure' with respect to polynomial operations?": "",
  "The result of adding, subtracting, or multiplying polynomials is always another polynomial": "",
  "The degree of the result is always the same as the inputs": "",
  "Polynomial operations can only be done in a certain order": "",
  "Polynomials always have a finite number of terms": "",
  "Polynomials are closed under addition, subtraction, and multiplication, meaning the result of any of these operations on polynomials is always another polynomial.": "",
  "A box has dimensions (x + 1), (x + 2), and (x + 3) centimeters. What is the volume of the box as a polynomial?": "",
  "x^3 + 6x^2 + 11x + 6": "",
  "x^3 + 6x^2 + 6x + 6": "",
  "3x + 6": "",
  "x^3 + 6": "",
  "V = (x+1)(x+2)(x+3). First: (x+1)(x+2) = x^2 + 3x + 2. Then (x^2 + 3x + 2)(x+3) = x^3 + 3x^2 + 3x^2 + 9x + 2x + 6 = x^3 + 6x^2 + 11x + 6.": "",
  "A picture frame has outer dimensions (2x + 4) by (x + 3) and inner dimensions (2x + 2) by (x + 1). What polynomial represents the area of the frame itself?": "",
  "4x^2 + 12": "",
  "6x + 10": "",
  "8x + 10": "",
  "2x^2 + 6x + 12": "",
  "Outer area: (2x+4)(x+3) = 2x^2 + 10x + 12. Inner area: (2x+2)(x+1) = 2x^2 + 4x + 2. Frame = (2x^2 + 10x + 12) - (2x^2 + 4x + 2) = 6x + 10.": "",
  "A storage container is a cube with side length (x + 5) feet. Express the surface area as a polynomial.": "",
  "6x^2 + 30x + 150": "",
  "x^3 + 15x^2 + 75x + 125": "",
  "6x^2 + 60x + 150": "",
  "x^2 + 10x + 25": "",
  "Surface area of a cube = 6s^2 = 6(x+5)^2 = 6(x^2 + 10x + 25) = 6x^2 + 60x + 150.": "",
  "A company's revenue from two products is R1 = 3x^2 + 10x and R2 = x^2 - 4x + 50. What is the total revenue?": "",
  "4x^2 - 6x + 50": "",
  "3x^4 + 6x + 50": "",
  "4x^2 + 14x + 50": "",
  "4x^2 + 6x + 50": "",
  "Total revenue = R1 + R2 = (3x^2 + x^2) + (10x - 4x) + 50 = 4x^2 + 6x + 50.": "",
  "A rectangular pool has length (3x + 1) meters and width (2x + 1) meters. A 1-meter-wide walkway surrounds it. What polynomial gives the total area including the walkway?": "",
  "6x^2 + 15x + 9": "",
  "6x^2 + 13x + 9": "",
  "6x^2 + 5x + 1": "",
  "6x^2 + 11x + 9": "",
  "With 1-meter walkway on each side, total length = 3x+3 and total width = 2x+3. Total area = (3x+3)(2x+3) = 6x^2 + 9x + 6x + 9 = 6x^2 + 15x + 9.": "",
  "A manufacturer's cost per item is (x + 5) dollars and they sell (x^2 - 3x + 10) items per day. What polynomial represents total daily cost?": "",
  "x^2 - 2x + 15": "",
  "x^3 + 2x^2 - 5x + 50": "",
  "x^3 - 3x^2 + 10x + 50": "",
  "x^3 + 2x^2 + 5x + 50": "",
  "Total cost = (x+5)(x^2-3x+10) = x^3 - 3x^2 + 10x + 5x^2 - 15x + 50 = x^3 + 2x^2 - 5x + 50.": "",
  "A building has a rectangular base of (4x - 1) by (3x + 2) meters and a triangular roof section. What is the area of just the base?": "",
  "12x^2 + 5x - 2": "",
  "12x^2 - 5x - 2": "",
  "7x^2 + 5x - 2": "",
  "12x^2 + 5x + 2": "",
  "Area = (4x-1)(3x+2) = 12x^2 + 8x - 3x - 2 = 12x^2 + 5x - 2.": "",
  "Two competing stores have weekly sales modeled by S1 = 4x^2 + 20x + 100 and S2 = 2x^2 + 35x + 80. By how much does Store 1 outsell Store 2?": "",
  "2x^2 - 15x + 20": "",
  "2x^2 + 15x + 20": "",
  "2x^2 - 15x - 20": "",
  "6x^2 + 55x + 180": "",
  "S1 - S2 = (4x^2 - 2x^2) + (20x - 35x) + (100 - 80) = 2x^2 - 15x + 20.": "",
  "A cylindrical tank has radius (x + 2) and height (x + 4). Using the formula V = pi*r^2*h, what polynomial (without pi) represents the volume factor?": "",
  "x^3 + 8x^2 + 20x + 16": "",
  "x^3 + 8x^2 + 16x + 16": "",
  "x^2 + 4x + 4": "",
  "r^2*h = (x+2)^2(x+4) = (x^2+4x+4)(x+4) = x^3 + 4x^2 + 4x^2 + 16x + 4x + 16 = x^3 + 8x^2 + 20x + 16.": "",
  "An investment returns (x^2 + 3x) dollars in the first year and (2x^2 - x + 500) dollars in the second year. If expenses are (x^2 + 100) each year, what is the total profit over two years?": "",
  "x^2 + 4x + 300": "",
  "x^2 + 2x + 300": "",
  "x^2 + 2x + 500": "",
  "3x^2 + 2x + 500": "",
  "Total returns = x^2 + 3x + 2x^2 - x + 500 = 3x^2 + 2x + 500. Total expenses = 2(x^2 + 100) = 2x^2 + 200. Profit = 3x^2 + 2x + 500 - 2x^2 - 200 = x^2 + 2x + 300.": ""
